data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction **won't compile**. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// EF Core 10
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All that expression tree plumbing is eliminated — EF Core 10 accepts `Action<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>` directly.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will append a number to disambiguate (e.g. `Street1`). This generates a column-rename migration.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** Your `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City` — it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Your implementation won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
    { /* logging — use logCommandText instead of command.CommandText for logs */ }
}
```

`logCommandText` contains a redacted version of the SQL (constants may be replaced) that's safe to log. Use `command.CommandText` only when you need the actual executed SQL.
